[{"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>There&#x27;s no excuse for ignoring the need to make your site accessible. As a developer it&#x27;s your responsibility to figure out how to incorporate accessibility into your workflows. You have the power! Here are a few easy ways to get started:</p>"}, "id": "e1c6308d-dc0c-460e-82cd-58dab70c85a4"}, {"type": "sub_heading_block", "value": {"sub_heading": "1. Add skip links"}, "id": "1fb664fd-533b-4b6a-b598-7edac4ee1cdb"}, {"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>Skip links are an excellent way to help keyboard users navigate your site more efficiently. They are the very first links a tabbing user will find available to them, so make them count! The two I always use are: <b>Skip to Content</b> and <b>Skip to Navigation</b>. The third one I have used on larger sites is: <b>Skip to Sitemap</b>. This would allow the user to get an overview of all the available pages without needed to filter through much content.</p><p>The code for adding skip links is super straightforward and easy to implement on any site. They will only display when focused on, but you can style them to match your design.</p>"}, "id": "1a1ffaab-8106-4e7e-968d-0fdb47332de7"}, {"type": "html_block", "value": {"html": "<pre>HTML</pre>"}, "id": "d621c94f-0d83-49d5-b619-c1c0a58167da"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "html", "code": "<div id="skiplinks" class="skiplinks" role="navigation">
  <a class="skip-content" href="#main-content">Skip to Content</a><br>
  <a class="skip-nav" href="#main-nav">Skip to Navigation</a>
</div>"}}, "id": "f26c095c-3023-4fbe-aaff-b463302679d9"}, {"type": "html_block", "value": {"html": "<pre>SCSS</pre>"}, "id": "61f74981-50e2-4f91-9138-8977b3cd1824"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "scss", "code": ".skiplinks {
  a {
    position: absolute !important;
    left: -999em;
    &:hover,
    &:visited {
      position: absolute !important;
      left: -999em;
    }
    &:active,
    &:focus {
      position: absolute;
      z-index: 999999;
      left: 10px;
    }
  }
}"}}, "id": "62742571-b8da-489d-af88-8d9ee0e7e451"}, {"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>Then just make sure your content container and nav container id&#x27;s match with your anchor links and you are good to go!</p>"}, "id": "8b094841-2d3a-4b75-a5c1-e537a38264ce"}, {"type": "sub_heading_block", "value": {"sub_heading": "2. Remove the focus outline for non-tabbing users <i>only</i>"}, "id": "a17096e6-8e8b-420b-86cb-1c3a79de2fcf"}, {"type": "html_block", "value": {"html": "<pre>Javascript</pre>"}, "id": "1e5097fd-5eb4-4333-851d-e5b1f479cef8"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "javascript", "code": "// RECOGNIZE A KEYBOARD USER
function handleFirstTab(e) {
  if (e.keyCode === 9) { // the "I am a keyboard user" key
    document.body.classList.add('user-is-tabbing');
    window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleFirstTab);
  }
}

window.addEventListener('keydown', handleFirstTab);"}}, "id": "262308af-447d-41a4-801a-c9932678ca17"}, {"type": "html_block", "value": {"html": "<pre>SCSS</pre>"}, "id": "94678076-3a88-4a99-936d-9d04ee8146a5"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "scss", "code": "body {
  &.user-is-tabbing {
    button,
    .btn,
    a {
      &:focus {
        outline: 5px auto $accent2 !important;
      }
    }
  }
}"}}, "id": "bd705d21-9d59-4842-9267-3576202b0a0c"}, {"type": "sub_heading_block", "value": {"sub_heading": "3. Limit your main menu to 6 items or less"}, "id": "a3eb749e-aea4-4754-b28d-6abe291c5a88"}, {"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>Depending on the size of your site, this may seem daunting or even impossible. But really ask yourself, what are people here do to? Try to focus on the basics.</p><p>If you must do a dropdown menu, please make sure that is is accessible via the keyboard. Here is an example of how that can be done:</p>"}, "id": "839b5db3-5642-4be0-bce4-61b7ac78201e"}, {"type": "html_block", "value": {"html": "<pre>Javascript</pre>"}, "id": "586d4b32-22ed-4974-a370-7d6dffff6c5e"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "javascript", "code": "$('.allow-toggle').focusin(function() {
  $(this).parents('.has-submenu').find('.dropdown-menu').css('display', 'block');
});

$('.dropdown-menu li:last-of-type .menu-link').focusout(function() {
  $(this).parents('.dropdown-menu').css('display', 'none');
});"}}, "id": "e01ae03c-f436-4d53-81e7-154a096acdc8"}, {"type": "html_block", "value": {"html": "<pre>HTML</pre>"}, "id": "13082169-f211-48aa-8e54-fdea64d81922"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "html", "code": "<div id="mainNav" class="collapse navbar-collapse" role="navigation" aria-label="Primary site navigation">
  <ul class="nav">
    <li class="presentation about has-submenu">
      <a href="/about/" class="menu-link allow-toggle">About</a>
      <ul class="dropdown-menu" role="menu">
        <li class="child-page"><a class="menu-link" href="/about/child-page/" role="menuitem">Child Page</a></li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>"}}, "id": "57911822-4863-4747-8f03-72e0272a6fb1"}]

[{"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>For most of my career I have been an almost exclusive user of <a href="https://fontawesome.com">Font Awesome</a>. More recently I started to feel like I needed something fresh to work with. I did some research and landed on testing out <a href="https://material.io/resources/icons/?style=baseline">Google&#x27;s Material Design Icons</a> on my next project.</p><p>It&#x27;s super easy to get started because you can just include them as a Google Font like so:</p>"}, "id": "43d0d8dd-0216-46b7-a782-af9e92ef6d42"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "html", "code": "<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">"}}, "id": "1af0b556-8b8f-4121-ab65-0a259331dff5"}, {"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>If you would rather include them a different way, the <a href="https://google.github.io/material-design-icons/">developer guide</a> explains how to directly download, use npm or bower, and more!</p><p>After using them in my HTML I realized I also wanted to use them in my CSS as :before and :after elements. Here&#x27;s a fun way you can do that:</p>"}, "id": "7fed986b-667c-4058-9a08-49834b68cbf8"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "css", "code": ".material-icons {
  direction: ltr;
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: 'Material Icons';
  font-size: 24px;
  font-style: normal;
  font-weight: normal;
  letter-spacing: normal;
  line-height: 1;
  text-transform: none;
  white-space: nowrap;
  word-wrap: normal;
  -webkit-font-feature-settings: 'liga';
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
}"}}, "id": "6637e45f-996a-4859-98ef-d030efef80fd"}, {"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>Then using SASS you can extend it and set the content using pseudo css elements:</p>"}, "id": "85953891-18a9-4657-b138-a819f9951595"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "scss", "code": "ul
  &:before {
    @extend .material-icons;
    content: 'label';
  }
}"}}, "id": "10cef7b8-831f-496b-a484-75d45ea0bd5f"}, {"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>I love how clean and modern these icons are and I&#x27;m excited to spice up my designs a little bit with something more than just Font Awesome (which I still use and love). Happy Devving!</p>"}, "id": "236cd7fb-f375-4cfb-879e-af5bde696c9f"}]

[{"type": "content_block", "value": {"content": "<p>Here is a little snippet of Javascript that I like to add to each of my projects to help improve accessibility. The issue with external links is they take a user to a completely new website, that may or may not have made accessibility a priority. Therefore, it&#x27;s important to alert the screen reader user that they are leaving your website when selecting an external link. This way they won&#x27;t unknowingly end up on a different site with which you have no control over. The easiest way to do this (in my opinion) is the following:</p>"}, "id": "275ff394-9174-4905-8c56-9ad09f10b569"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "javascript", "code": "setTimeout(function() {
    $('a[target="_blank"]').addClass('external-link');
    $('.external-link').append(' <span class="sr-only"> External link - Opens in new window</span>');
}, 100);"}}, "id": "b9b33d41-892a-432a-a129-f1e54a97d90a"}, {"type": "html_block", "value": {"html": "<p>The very short timeout is added just to make sure all the links are loaded on the page before adding the necessary class. The <code>sr-only</code> class is built into <a target="_blank" href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/utilities/screenreaders/">Bootstrap</a>, so if you aren't using Bootstrap you should also add the following to your css:</p>"}, "id": "ba1f1c52-6f33-46a7-9393-defeb6156b4b"}, {"type": "code_block", "value": {"code": {"language": "scss", "code": ".sr-only {
  border: 0;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  height: 1px;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  padding: 0;
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
}"}}, "id": "60bc577d-5421-40cb-ae16-12cabd68da6c"}]
